   <conbody>
      <div class="- topic/div ">
         <p class="- topic/p ">In a redundant system it is possible to have a common battery
bank.<ph platform="PxW" class="- topic/ph "> With this option both units have individual
battery breakers and can have common or individual battery protection
breakers.</ph>
            <ph platform="SDC" class="- topic/ph "> With this option both units have
a common battery breaker and/or a common battery protection breaker.
The battery current for both units will be measured at the same point.</ph>
         </p>
         <note platform="SDC" class="- topic/note ">With a common battery the rectifier output
switches are placed before the battery connection.</note>
